==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jeffersonian simplicity
<hw>Jeffersonian simplicity</hw>. <def>The absence of pomp or display
which Jefferson aimed at in his administration as President (1801-1809),
eschewing display or ceremony tending to distinguish the President from
the people, as in going to the capital on horseback and with no escort,
the abolition of court etiquette and the weekly levee, refusal to
recognize titles of honor, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jeffersonite</ent>⟦br⟧
